:>Is it simply a matter of specifying a
:>larger key size when using PGP?  
:
:Bigger keys mean exponentially increasing difficulty in breaking the cypher.
 
This is false. Both the quadratic sieve and number field sieve (as well as
ECM) are sub-exponential algorithms.

:We were all nubies sometime.
 
And some still are, even though they think otherwise.

1024 bits is not nearly enough for military secrets, some of which demand
absolute security for 50 years or more.

